1
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:05,933
<i>Marj, I was honestly
about to tell you, but...</i>

2
00:00:06,067 --> 00:00:08,100
<i> [SLAPS]</i>

3
00:00:08,233 --> 00:00:11,433
<i>How many times are you going
to make a fool out of me?</i>

4
00:00:11,567 --> 00:00:14,100
<i> I will never forgive you!</i>

5
00:00:14,233 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> It looks like Yolly
is determined to get back at us.</i>

6
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>Be afraid now, my dear husband,</i>

7
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> because you are the one
with a closet full of skeletons.</i>

8
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:23,733
<i> You are far too complacent.</i>

9
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:25,333
<i>Do you really have nothing
to hide?</i>

10
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,800
<i>- Jas.
- Because of your mom again,</i>

11
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:30,367
<i>my parents are fighting
once more.</i>

12
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,800
<i> You're just like your mother.</i>

13
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:34,100
<i>You like to suck the happiness
out of others.</i>

14
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,567
<i>If Ashley and Jasmine
are siblings,</i>

15
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:37,800
<i> there's a high chance</i>

16
00:00:37,933 --> 00:00:40,300
<i>they will be a match
for a bone marrow transplant.</i>

17
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:44,433
<i>Tell me what I need to do
so you will not leave.</i>

18
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:48,067
<i>Convince Thea to allow Ashley
to get tested.</i>

19
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:51,233
<i>If not, you will lose
Jasmine too.</i>

20
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,667
<i> Stay here for now, okay?</i>

21
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:42,133
Do not get involved
in that chaos.

22
00:02:00,033 --> 00:02:02,667
[DRAMATIC]

23
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,733
- Jas.
- Because of your mom again,

24
00:02:05,867 --> 00:02:08,733
my parents are fighting.

25
00:02:08,867 --> 00:02:10,933
You really are alike.

26
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:14,167
You like to suck the happiness
out of others.

27
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,533
You love destroying other
people's relationship.

28
00:02:16,667 --> 00:02:19,067
Jas, this is unfair.

29
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:23,967
I never intended to ruin
your happiness.

30
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:27,133
All I ever did was support you.

31
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:29,900
Always be there for you.

32
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:32,200
But it just so happened that

33
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:35,933
you saw someone you like
be there for me too.

34
00:02:36,067 --> 00:02:38,533
But why does it feel like
I am the one at fault?

35
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:40,467
Because you let it happen.

36
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,500
You let Xander fall for you.

37
00:02:42,633 --> 00:02:45,167
I did not let
anything happen, Jas.

38
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,533
It just happened.

39
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,333
I was already distancing myself
from Xander

40
00:02:50,467 --> 00:02:52,500
out of respect for you.

41
00:02:52,633 --> 00:02:56,500
Because our friendship matters
more to me than any guy.

42
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:00,567
But you?

43
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,500
Why does Xander seem
more important to you

44
00:03:03,633 --> 00:03:05,600
than everything we shared?

45
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:08,933
Now that my world is shattering
into pieces

46
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:12,967
because of everything
we learned today,

47
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:16,400
all I want is for my best friend
to be there for me.

48
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:22,267
Yet this is what I hear
from you.

49
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,700
Because whenever I look
at you...

50
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:31,533
all I see is the daughter of the
person who ruined my parents.

51
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,467
All I see is someone who steals
others, just like her mother.

52
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,800
The person who could also
destroy my life someday.

53
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:43,333
I would never do that to you,
Jasmine.

54
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:44,733
You say that now.

55
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:48,167
But I no longer trust you, Ash.

56
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:52,533
And that is why I do not want
to be best friends anymore.

57
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:56,033
And I will never accept you
as my sibling.

58
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,433
Leave me alone!

59
00:03:57,567 --> 00:03:59,300
Get out! Get out!

60
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:00,233
Jas.

61
00:04:00,367 --> 00:04:03,100
[DRAMATIC]

62
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:05,033
[SOBBING]

63
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:26,033
Marj, please. Marj, I was
honestly about to tell you,

64
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:28,767
- but...
- [SLAPS]

65
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:30,733
How many times, Paolo?

66
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:34,733
How many times will you make
a fool out of me?

67
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:39,133
Do you enjoy hurting me?

68
00:04:39,267 --> 00:04:40,533
You have no shame!

69
00:04:40,667 --> 00:04:43,000
You are worthless!
Do not touch me!

70
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:45,100
- Marj, please.
- [SOBBING]

71
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:52,467
What did I do?

72
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:59,067
What did I do for you
to treat me like this?

73
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,133
Nothing.

74
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:04,367
Marj, you did nothing wrong.

75
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:09,267
I am the one at fault.
You are right!

76
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:13,433
But I will never stop
apologizing to you.

77
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,067
No!

78
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,200
I will never forgive you!

79
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:24,767
I would rather endure
God's punishment

80
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:29,100
than give you another chance
to deceive me again.

81
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,667
I will not allow it anymore!

82
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:34,967
[SOBBING]

83
00:05:38,367 --> 00:05:40,533
[OST]

84
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:45,700
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

85
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,867
My child, did you take
your medicine?

86
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:11,967
Mom, I just took it.

87
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:15,033
Your back, why is it wet?

88
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,067
This is not okay, wait.

89
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,167
Mom...

90
00:06:20,033 --> 00:06:21,167
it is okay.

91
00:06:24,633 --> 00:06:27,333
- It is not okay.
- It's okay, Mom.

92
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,567
Just cry.

93
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:34,600
[SOBBING]

94
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:40,133
[DRAMATIC]

95
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,000
Ashley.

96
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,267
Can we talk?

97
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,233
I just want to explain.

98
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:41,833
Sorry, but...

99
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:44,633
I still need to pack
my mom's things.

100
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:47,833
She cannot come in here anymore.

101
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,467
Everyone has abandoned her.

102
00:07:58,267 --> 00:08:00,133
But you are still here.

103
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:03,767
Still safe.

104
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:09,167
As if you did nothing wrong.

105
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:15,633
And you did not defend my mom.

106
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:20,700
As if you weren't together
in the mistake you made.

107
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:22,767
Ashley, it is complicated.

108
00:08:25,067 --> 00:08:28,467
Your mother and I should have
never made that mistake.

109
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,267
Not that I'm calling you
a mistake, it's just...

110
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,133
I do not want to hear it.

111
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:35,467
I am sorry.

112
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,433
[SOBBING]

113
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:44,133
I just want peace of mind
right now.

114
00:08:49,267 --> 00:08:52,067
That is why it is better
for us to leave.

115
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:55,500
So the chaos can finally stop.

116
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:59,533
[SOBBING]

117
00:08:59,667 --> 00:09:02,200
Ashley, please,
let us talk first.

118
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,700
Do not call me that!

119
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:16,433
I'm sorry, Uncle Paolo.

120
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:20,700
You may be my biological father,
but dad is still my father.

121
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:23,767
Your sibling.

122
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,967
My mom's spouse.

123
00:09:29,033 --> 00:09:30,833
That will never change.

124
00:09:30,967 --> 00:09:35,300
[SOBBING]

125
00:09:42,667 --> 00:09:44,400
Ashley, wait!

126
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:45,533
My child.

127
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:48,467
[ASHLEY SOBBING]

128
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:52,767
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:55,867
[SOBBING]

130
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:01,733
You are all useless!

131
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:04,433
Yolly already got
into this house,

132
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:06,100
and she still managed to escape!

133
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:10,200
Our family fell into chaos
because of your incompetence!

134
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:13,000
Sorry, Sir,
we really did not notice.

135
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:14,500
You are all fired!

136
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:15,700
Leave now!

137
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:19,167
[INTENSE]

138
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:25,233
It looks like Yolly
is determined to get back at us.

139
00:10:26,533 --> 00:10:28,733
She already started with Paolo.

140
00:10:28,867 --> 00:10:31,733
Who knows what else she will do?

141
00:10:31,867 --> 00:10:34,467
What other secrets
will she reveal to the world?

142
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:37,633
Be afraid now, my dear husband.

143
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:41,833
Because you are the one
with a closet full of skeletons.

144
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:43,700
Now you know,

145
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:47,200
when a woman who has been silent
for a long time gets angry.

146
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,933
She does not just dig up bones.

147
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:52,400
She exhumes.

148
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:54,133
[CHUCKLES]

149
00:10:55,767 --> 00:10:57,667
You are too complacent.

150
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,567
Why?

151
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,600
Do you have nothing to hide?

152
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:05,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

153
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:16,367
I cannot believe
they did this to me.

154
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:22,433
They let that woman
humiliate me.

155
00:11:24,933 --> 00:11:28,567
They banished me from the house
even though you were there.

156
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,033
Mom.

157
00:11:36,167 --> 00:11:38,633
You know why they did that
to you.

158
00:11:40,467 --> 00:11:41,767
It is your fault.

159
00:11:43,333 --> 00:11:44,733
And Paolo's.

160
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:55,133
I do not know why mom and dad
had to interfere in our mess.

161
00:11:57,767 --> 00:12:00,100
They even sided with that woman.

162
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:05,000
I no longer have a spouse...

163
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:08,367
I no longer have a home,

164
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,967
and I am sure I will also lose
my job too.

165
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:17,033
There is nothing left for me.

166
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,200
[SOBBING]

167
00:12:21,333 --> 00:12:23,233
But I am here.

168
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,100
You are right.

169
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:40,933
You are right, my child.

170
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,000
Forgive me.

171
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:54,867
I am sorry for lying to you
about your real father.

172
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:03,733
I refuse to know that, Mom.

173
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:07,500
Dad is still my father.

174
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:11,033
Edward Torrecampo.

175
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:14,200
That will never change.

176
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,033
I wish he was here.

177
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,900
And I really miss him.

178
00:13:23,467 --> 00:13:26,533
And I am sorry that your father
is not here.

179
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:32,767
I am sorry for all the mistakes
I made.

180
00:13:35,367 --> 00:13:38,133
It is okay, Mom.

181
00:13:38,267 --> 00:13:39,900
We will get through this...

182
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,367
together.

183
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:49,667
[DRAMATIC]

184
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:53,300
You are the only good thing left
in my life, Ashley.

185
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:59,533
I will not allow myself
to lose you.

186
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,833
I will not allow it, my child.

187
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:09,767
I do not want to lose you.

188
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:17,467
[SIGHS]

189
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:27,567
[DRAMATIC]

190
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,167
Sir, thank you for listening
to our pitch.

191
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,767
I am looking forward
to our future partnership.

192
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,367
You are welcome.

193
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:36,333
Thank you, Sir.

194
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:37,467
I will go ahead.

195
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,600
All right, Sir.

196
00:14:40,267 --> 00:14:41,233
Hey!

197
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:42,700
You have been
on your phone nonstop.

198
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:44,500
It is embarrassing in front
of the client.

199
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:46,467
Someone sent me a link.

200
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:49,467
What is it?

201
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,133
Edward, just a heads-up.

202
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:55,167
I do not think you will like
what is in the video.

203
00:14:56,633 --> 00:14:57,467
Give it to me.

204
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:04,200
This woman is none other than
Thea Villareal Torrecampo.

205
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:08,833
She stole my spouse
and got pregnant by him.

206
00:15:08,967 --> 00:15:14,267
Shame does not exist for her
because she made her spouse,

207
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:16,100
who is my spouse's sibling,

208
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:18,467
take responsibility
for their depravity.

209
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:21,267
What?

210
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,233
You want me to stop, Paolo?

211
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:25,267
Wow!

212
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:28,267
She's shameless.

213
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:32,067
I knew Thea was hiding
a deep secret.

214
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:35,600
You're right.

215
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:38,500
That woman brings misfortune.

216
00:15:41,900 --> 00:15:43,567
I feel bad for you...

217
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:50,133
You're already distraught trying
to find a donor for Jasmine.

218
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:55,000
It even turned out that Ashley
is the child of Paolo and Thea.

219
00:15:55,133 --> 00:15:56,833
Can you still breathe?

220
00:15:56,967 --> 00:15:59,833
I have no choice
but to endure it.

221
00:16:01,133 --> 00:16:02,100
Wait, Marj.

222
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,467
If Ashley and Jasmine
are siblings...

223
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,700
there's a high chance

224
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:10,767
they will be a match
for a bone marrow transplant.

225
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:17,233
You are right.

226
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:21,767
Ashley might be the one
who can save Jasmine.

227
00:16:21,900 --> 00:16:28,367
[INTENSE]

228
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,133
Just eat.

229
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:32,467
Mom...

230
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,100
it is a good thing

231
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:38,200
I am no longer studying
at my old school.

232
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,200
Why?

233
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:46,033
My former classmates messaged me
about the video.

234
00:16:47,433 --> 00:16:49,600
I think they are also making fun
of me.

235
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:50,767
[SIGHS]

236
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:56,267
My child, I am so sorry.

237
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:59,067
This is Marj's fault.

238
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:01,467
Do not worry,

239
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,133
I will make it up to you.

240
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:06,533
[DOORBELL RINGS]

241
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:09,933
Who is that?

242
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:12,400
[INTENSE]

243
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,533
Edward.

244
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,900
- Ashley?
- Dad?

245
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:28,200
- Dad.
- [SOBBING]

246
00:17:31,533 --> 00:17:32,967
Dad.

247
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:38,000
I am so happy that you're here.

248
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:42,233
[DRAMATIC]

249
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,433
Marj.

250
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:56,800
Marj, what are you doing?

251
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:59,533
What do you think? I am packing.

252
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:01,467
You do not have to do this.

253
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:05,100
You cannot take Jasmine
away from the family.

254
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:07,667
She needs this house,
the comfort.

255
00:18:10,433 --> 00:18:12,867
Paolo, after everything,

256
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,967
do you think Jasmine and I
will still be comfortable here?

257
00:18:16,100 --> 00:18:20,967
Fine, tell me what I need to do
so you will not leave.

258
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,200
[SIGHS]

259
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:26,333
If you want a chance
to change my mind,

260
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:28,167
there is one thing you need
to do.

261
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:29,500
Please,

262
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,067
tell me.

263
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:35,700
Convince Thea to let Ashley
get tested

264
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:38,900
and become Jasmine's donor
if they match.

265
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:43,167
How can I do that if I turn
my back on her for you?

266
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,667
Marj, she will be even
less willing.

267
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:50,333
That is all you need to do.

268
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:53,467
So that is what you need to fix.

269
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:57,067
[INTENSE]

270
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:03,733
Marj, it is not that easy.

271
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:04,800
Why?

272
00:19:06,233 --> 00:19:07,933
Is this easy for me, Paolo?

273
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:09,233
Do you think so?

274
00:19:10,300 --> 00:19:11,533
Marj, Thea already refused.

275
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:14,700
Even if I am Ashley's
biological father,

276
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:17,600
Edward is still
her legal parent.

277
00:19:17,733 --> 00:19:20,800
And Ashley is already
very confused.

278
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,833
I do not want to add
more pressure on her.

279
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:26,233
You pity Ashley, but you do not
pity our child.

280
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:27,600
What is wrong with you, Paolo?

281
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:29,333
Time is ticking.

282
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:35,167
While you pity Thea's child, our
child is slowly slipping away.

283
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:37,667
Maybe there is another way.

284
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,600
I will look for another donor.

285
00:19:39,733 --> 00:19:41,533
Love, please, do not...

286
00:19:41,667 --> 00:19:43,033
Do not leave.

287
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:48,533
Our family needs to be whole
right now because if you leave,

288
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:50,733
we will completely fall apart.

289
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:52,600
- [SLAPS]
- How dare you!

290
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,400
You destroyed us
from the very beginning.

291
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:57,633
And you want Jasmine and me
to stay here?

292
00:19:57,767 --> 00:19:59,333
No!

293
00:19:59,467 --> 00:20:01,833
In a family, wherever you move,

294
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:05,467
the lies will still stink.

295
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:10,200
As far as I am concerned, Paolo,

296
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:11,700
our marriage is over

297
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:14,167
and I am done
being a Torrecampo.

298
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,433
- Marj.
- Do not touch me!

299
00:20:18,667 --> 00:20:21,933
If you want even the smallest
chance for me to treat you

300
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:23,833
as my child's father,

301
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:28,200
convince Thea to allow Ashley
to get tested.

302
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:31,467
If not, you will lose
Jasmine too.

303
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:41,567
[INTENSE]

304
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:01,733
My child.

305
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,333
My child.

306
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,400
I am sorry.

307
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:11,200
I am only telling you
the truth now.

308
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,900
Have you known
for a long time, Dad?

309
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,033
[SIGHS]

310
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:25,500
Sort of...

311
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,433
I only found out recently too.

312
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:31,233
When I found out...

313
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:35,267
I did not know how to tell you
because...

314
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,167
because I did not want you
to be hurt by our mistake.

315
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,967
What about us, Dad?

316
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:50,333
You are still my child.

317
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:54,567
I am still your father.

318
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,333
Nothing will change that.

319
00:21:58,767 --> 00:22:00,400
I took care of you.

320
00:22:00,533 --> 00:22:02,233
I raised you.

321
00:22:05,133 --> 00:22:07,100
I took you to school.

322
00:22:08,233 --> 00:22:10,833
Whenever you were sick,
I stayed by your side.

323
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,167
That can never be erased,
my child.

324
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:19,500
What about you and mom?

325
00:22:21,767 --> 00:22:24,467
What she did to me was deeper
than a wound.

326
00:22:27,067 --> 00:22:29,233
It was not just a simple
mistake, my child.

327
00:22:32,633 --> 00:22:34,633
But you know...

328
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:35,867
sometimes...

329
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:40,600
two people become better
parents...

330
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,167
when they are not together.

331
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:49,000
[DRAMATIC]

332
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,800
No matter what...

333
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:57,133
you're still my father.

334
00:22:57,267 --> 00:23:02,067
- [SOBBING]
- [DRAMATIC]

335
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:06,800
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:33,433
Marj.

337
00:23:33,567 --> 00:23:35,000
What is this?

338
00:23:35,133 --> 00:23:37,167
I thought we already resolved
the problem?

339
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:39,033
Thea is no longer here.

340
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:42,200
We pity our grandchild.

341
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:43,700
She is sick.

342
00:23:43,833 --> 00:23:48,033
She needs stability,
not another unnecessary chaos.

343
00:23:48,167 --> 00:23:49,900
Stability?

344
00:23:50,033 --> 00:23:52,067
When did this family
ever become stable?

345
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:53,933
No one is leaving this house.

346
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:57,000
When a family has problems,

347
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:58,767
you do not run away from them.

348
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,233
You fix them inside the home.

349
00:24:01,767 --> 00:24:03,867
Especially the problems...

350
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,433
you brought to us.

351
00:24:06,633 --> 00:24:09,967
Fix them inside or hide them?

352
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:13,467
Dad, this is not the first time
you fixed things.

353
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:16,333
First, you covered up Paolo's
infidelity

354
00:24:16,467 --> 00:24:19,033
and you also hid the fact
that Ashley is his child.

355
00:24:20,067 --> 00:24:21,067
Marj,

356
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:25,367
not all truths need
to be revealed right away.

357
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:29,900
There are times when more people
will get hurt.

358
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:33,567
We did that to protect you.

359
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:35,967
Protect us?

360
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:37,967
Or protect your surname?

361
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:42,967
[INTENSE]

362
00:24:43,233 --> 00:24:44,200
Jasmine, let's go.

363
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:45,733
I am sorry.

364
00:24:45,867 --> 00:24:48,833
Maybe it is better if we are not
together for now.

365
00:24:50,233 --> 00:24:52,200
It has become too toxic.

366
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,667
No.

367
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:55,633
No.

368
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:59,100
This family will not fall apart

369
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:00,400
just because of drama.

370
00:25:01,433 --> 00:25:02,400
Marj...

371
00:25:03,700 --> 00:25:04,900
go inside.

372
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:06,967
Now!

373
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:10,300
- [INTENSE]
- Dad, please.

374
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:11,500
Let them go.

375
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:15,000
[INTENSE]

376
00:25:15,133 --> 00:25:16,333
What did you say?

377
00:25:17,633 --> 00:25:19,967
You will really let your spouse
and child leave you?

378
00:25:22,633 --> 00:25:25,600
Let them go.

379
00:25:25,733 --> 00:25:28,667
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

380
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:33,033
I am still the head
of this house.

381
00:25:33,167 --> 00:25:34,500
And I will be obeyed.

382
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,900
And that was my mistake.

383
00:25:39,033 --> 00:25:40,867
I listened to you.

384
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,067
I obeyed you.

385
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,500
And I let my family fall apart.

386
00:25:47,767 --> 00:25:49,933
[INTENSE]

387
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:53,767
<i> Excuse me.</i>

388
00:25:57,133 --> 00:26:00,567
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

389
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:08,167
For a child, you'd do anything.

390
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,533
What are you doing here?

391
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:11,833
We really need Ashley
to get tested.

392
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:13,400
Because if they match,

393
00:26:13,533 --> 00:26:15,633
this is Jasmine's best chance.

394
00:26:15,767 --> 00:26:18,000
I will not gamble
my child's safety.

395
00:26:18,133 --> 00:26:19,833
Ashley is not your child.

396
00:26:19,967 --> 00:26:22,567
You lived without Ashley
for years,

397
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:24,000
and now that you need her,

398
00:26:24,133 --> 00:26:25,767
you suddenly want to act
like a father?

399
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:27,233
We are running out of time.

400
00:26:27,367 --> 00:26:28,267
Do something!

401
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:31,000
If you need to plead
with Ashley, then plead.

402
00:26:31,133 --> 00:26:32,967
We are all doing the best
we can.

403
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:34,567
Well, it is not enough.

404
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:35,900
<i> You do not get it, Paolo.</i>

405
00:26:36,033 --> 00:26:37,133
This is your karma.

406
00:26:37,267 --> 00:26:39,333
<i>Your karma is that your child
might die</i>

407
00:26:39,467 --> 00:26:42,700
because you are greedy,
deceitful, and arrogant!

408
00:26:42,867 --> 00:26:44,900
- [THUDS]
- I already pleaded.

409
00:26:45,033 --> 00:26:47,600
But Edward and Thea
still refused.

410
00:26:47,733 --> 00:26:50,000
That is why I already spoke
to dad.

411
00:26:50,133 --> 00:26:51,800
That was the only thing
you had to do,

412
00:26:51,933 --> 00:26:54,300
and you still could not do it
on your own?

413
00:26:54,433 --> 00:26:57,000
You hid the truth
for sixteen years,

414
00:26:57,133 --> 00:26:59,033
now that you have a chance
to make up for it,

415
00:26:59,167 --> 00:27:00,533
you still do nothing.

416
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:03,300
If you want to secure
your child's future,

417
00:27:03,433 --> 00:27:05,000
there is one thing you can do.

418
00:27:05,133 --> 00:27:06,567
Agree to have Ashley tested.

419
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:09,767
<i>You are using my child
as payment for my sins?</i>

420
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:11,467
<i> I am not using my grandchild.</i>

421
00:27:11,600 --> 00:27:13,000
<i> That is her role now.</i>

422
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:16,033
So, if you want anything left
to you, Thea, and to your child,

423
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,767
agree to have Ashley tested.

424
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,233
Everything will be easy

425
00:27:19,367 --> 00:27:20,867
if you just obey.

426
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:25,533
[INTENSE]
